window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Protecting her identity means life or death in this immersive epic fantasy inspired by the Mughal Empire. </b></p> <p>In a different life, under a different name, Razia Khan was raised to be the crown prince of Nizam, the most powerful kingdom in Daryastan. Born with the soul of a woman, she ran away at a young age to escape her father’s hatred and live life true to herself. </p> <p>Among the hijras of Bikampur, Razia finds sisterhood and discovers a new purpose in life. By day she’s one of her dera’s finest dancers and by night its most profitable thief. But when her latest target leads her to cross paths with Arjun Agnivansha, prince of Bikampur, it is she who has something stolen. </p> <p>An immediate connection with the prince changes Razia’s life forever, and she finds herself embroiled in a dangerous political war. The stakes are greater than any heist she’s ever performed. When the battle brings her face-to-face with her father, Razia has the chance to reclaim everything she lost...and save her prince.</p>"; 
